<p>Excerpts from Mark Twain&#8217;s boyhood journal:</p>
<p>Monday &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Tuesday &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Wednesday &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Thursday &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Friday &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Next Friday &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Friday fortnight &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.<br />
Following month &#8212; Got up, washed, went to bed.</p>
<p>&#8220;I stopped, then, discouraged. Startling events appeared to be too rare, in my career, to render a diary necessary.&#8221;</p>
<p>(From <a href="https://www.gutenberg.org/cache/epub/3176/pg3176.txt"><em>The Innocents Abroad</em></a>.)</p>
